			<abstract>
				<p>Letter from Gerta Sachsová addressed to family friends. Sachsová was deported with her husband from Prague to the Theresienstadt
					Ghetto in July 1943, from where she was sent to Auschwitz in autumn 1944. Her parents and husband perished. Sachsová describes
					their fate and her difficult postwar adaptation.</p>
			</abstract>

